query.result:
127 Then I did like those who go 128 with something on their head that they do not know about, 129 except that the gestures of others make them suspect;
130 so that the hand helps to make sure, 131 and seeks and finds and performs that task 132 that cannot be accomplished by sight;
133 and with the fingers of my right hand, one by one, 134 I found indeed the six letters that he of the keys 135 had incised on my temples:
136 at which, looking, my leader smiled.
